maintext:
Person escapes from house fire in Wolfeboro, no injuries
WOLFEBORO, N.H. (AP) — One person was able to get out of a house that was on fire in Wolfeboro, New Hampshire, authorities said Wednesday.
WMUR-TV reports firefighters were called at about 2:30 a.m. Wednesday. They found heavy flames in the basement, and the flames spread to the first floor.
No injuries were reported.
The fire is under investigation.
